3. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the use of computation to reconstruct hidden geometry, which is relevant to robotics applications such as mapping and localization. 
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper involves geometric computations such as voxelization and intersection of manifolds, which are core topics in computational geometry. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with imaging and signal processing techniques, which are relevant to multimedia applications such as image and video processing.
